docs.lead_paragraph: Philadelphia and Newark papers assure us that Asiatic cholera is quite prevalent in this City. From the former city we heard the announcement some fortnight since, and at once took special pains to inquire how far it was true. The results are that we hear of five or seven cases of well-marked cholera

headline.main: TEMPERANCE DISCUSSIONS.; Meeting of the Women's City Temperance Alltance.

docs.lead_paragraph: A meeting of the Women's City Temperanoe Alliance was held at No. 15 Laight-street on Tuesday. There were about twenty ladies present. At 3 o'clock P. M., the meeting was called to order by Mrs. T. S. MARTIN, President of the Society.

headline.main: THE OPERA LIBEL CASE.; Edward P. Fry agt. James Gordon Bennett. SUPERIOR COURT

docs.lead_paragraph: SUPERIOR COURT-FIRST PAST. Before lion. Chief Justice Oakley. FIFTH DAY. DEFPIDANT'S CASE. The Court met at 10 A. M. yesterday morning. The following depositions were then read: DEPOSITION OF MADAME TRUFFI BENEDETTI. The examination of Theresa Truffi Benedetti produced, sworn, end examined conditionally, on the part of the defendaut, in pursuance of the foregoing order is the above entitled cause. New-York, June 12, 1852.

byline.original: Special Dispatch to the New-York Daily Times:

docs.lead_paragraph: The following is an extract from a letter to a friend in Madison County: NEW-YORK, Nov. 29, 1853. The disease in my head continues una??ted. My New York physicians (how justly I do not know) believe it is a consequence of the surgical operation to which I submitted just Winter That skillful operation relieved me entirely of a painful disease; but it is, perhaps a worse one which has come upon me.
